                            <comment id="13772540" author="stack" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 01:00:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This will not work w/ the way we now package hbase; you must pick an hadoop1 or hadoop2 hbase (I doubt it ever worked; we never were able to package up in mvn an hbase w/ the right compat includes in the pom).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772542" author="enis" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 01:07:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch, which might be a solution to the issue. Now profiles use hbase.hadoop.version instead. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772545" author="enis" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 01:17:42 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will not work w/ the way we now package hbase; you must pick an hadoop1 or hadoop2 hbase (I doubt it ever worked; we never were able to package up in mvn an hbase w/ the right compat includes in the pom).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hold on, let me check whether I have published locally with the generated poms. I thought I did. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772552" author="enis" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 01:26:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, this turned out to be not a problem. Even if downstream project uses hadoop.profile, it seems that it does not activate/deactivate the profile in hbase pom which is a dependency. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mvn -Dhadoop.profile=2 -Dhbase.version=0.96.0-hadoop2 dependency:tree&lt;br/&gt;
works fine. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
